<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="461" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">Etymology.</emphasis>
This specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang &amp; Wang &amp; Guan" authorityYear="2021" box="[860,977,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Heliodinidae" genus="Stathmopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyriformis">
<emphasis box="[860,977,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="461">pyriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, referring to the shape of the corpus bursae.
</paragraph>
